  "prompt": "I mean, money laundering is definitely illegal, isn't it?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is definitely illegal. It is a criminal activity that involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. The funds are often derived from illegal activities such as drug trafficking, corruption, fraud, or organized crime. The purpose of money laundering is to make the money appear as if it comes from legitimate sources.\n\nMoney laundering is prohibited by law in almost every country around the world. In the United States, for example, it is primarily addressed under the Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) and the Money Laundering Control Act (MLCA). The penalties for money laundering can be severe, including substantial fines and lengthy prison sentences. International organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) also work to set global standards for combating money laundering and terrorist financing.",
